HEADWORD: Regicide
<hw>Reg"i*cide</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧j"⟦icr⟧*s⟦imac⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧gicide</ets>; L. <ets>rex</ets>,
<ets>regis</ets>, a king + <ets>caedere</ets> to kill. Cf.
<er>Homicide</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who kills or who murders
a king; specifically <fld>(Eng. Hist.)</fld>, one of the judges who
condemned <person>Charles I.</person> to death.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The killing or the murder of a king.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

